Verify the ability to search for a chat	1. Open the application.
2. Locate the Search Bar in the left panel.
3. Enter a keyword matching an existing chat.
4. Press Enter or click the search icon.	• The search should return all chats containing the exact keyword.
• The matching word should be highlighted inside the chat history results.
• The search should be case-insensitive (e.g., searching for "Meeting" or "meeting" should return the same results).
• If multiple chats match, all should be displayed in descending order of relevance (latest chats first).
• The UI should remain clear, and search results should be easy to scroll through.
